The Kiss of Artemis Photo: Courtesy of Li ZiChinese artist Li Zi released a new installation inspired by Greek myth about Artemis in Beijing on Sunday. The magnetic levitation piece called The Kiss of Artemis includes the kissing boy and girl inspired by the romantic tragedy between Artemis and Orion, who are floating on a stone pillar magically. Curated by Guo Yingna, the exhibition in downtown Beijing also includes the artist' various pieces like Babylon Gardens as well as 160 Decibel, her signature piece, the lion and tiger from which have been used in a new series of crossover designs by fashion designer Liu Ruowei. The exhibition is set to run March 31.